doc.previous: Skin friction drag arises from the friction of the fluid against the skin of the object that is moving through it Skin friction arises from the interaction between the fluid and the skin of the body and is directly related to the wetted surface the area of the surface of the body that is in contact with the fluid As with other components of parasitic drag skin friction follows the drag equation and rises with the square of the velocity
